01/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- EUROFOR officially assumed command of the EU military mission Concordia from France during a ceremony Tuesday (30 September) at NATO headquarters in Skopje. 
Portuguese Major General Luis Nelson Ferreira dos Santos will head Concordia until its mandate expires on 15 December. 
Afterwards, the EU will send in a new 200-strong police mission for a year.
In other news Tuesday, European Parliament Speaker Pat Cox arrived in Macedonia as part of his tour of the Balkans. 
He is to discuss issues related EU membership aspirations, progress since the June EU summit in Thessaloniki, and possibilities for enhancing regional co-operation. 
(Dnevnik - 01/10/03; MIA, A1 TV, Makfax - 30/09/03)
